</table><div style="margin:15px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><p>Since version 1.3.3 there is an additional selection field.<br />
<br />
Under <strong>template </strong>you can create templates for the content part &quot;Plain text&quot;. With this possibility&nbsp; you can create several templates for different parts.<br />
<br />
You can find a standard template under<br />
<br />
a. If you use e newly installed version 1.3.3:<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>template/inc_cntpart/plaintext<br />
<br />
</strong>b. If you use an upgraded version: <strong><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; template/inc_cntpart/plaintext<br />
<br />
</strong>Only a person with access to the server/webspace can change the templates.<br />
<br />
The source code of the standard template looks like this:<br />
<br />
<strong>[TITLE]&lt;h4&gt;{TITLE}&lt;/h4&gt;[/TITLE]<br />
[SUBTITLE]&lt;h5&gt;{SUBTITLE}&lt;/h5&gt;[/SUBTITLE]<br />
[TEXT]&lt;p&gt;{TEXT}&lt;/p&gt;[/TEXT]</strong></p><div style="margin:10px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><p><font color="#ff0000">Notice for Templates:<br />
This content part has an own template. It is recommended when you change the standard template to rename it and to use the renamed template. Then you do not have any problems with an update and your template will not be overwritten.<br />
</font></p><div align="right"><a href="#top"><img src="img/article/top_link_0.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></div>
